nsolidation and automated PO approval workflows. UXUI Transformation: Partnered with UX researchers to redesign the clinician portal.\nUsed\ndata-driven analysis of click-paths to reduce documentation time for nurses by 15 minutes\nper shift. Executive Reporting: Built a real-time Transformation KPI dashboard in\nTableau for the\nclients Board of Directors. Provided visibility into project burn-rates, risk mitigation, and re-", "start_date": null, "end_date": null, "is_current": true}, {"job_title": "alized business value. Senior Business Systems Analyst  FinEdge Solutions", "company_name": "New York, NY (Financial Technology  Core Banking Infrastructure)", "description": "Role Overview: Primary analytical lead for the Global-Pay initiative, focusing on high-frequency\npayment processing and regulatory reporting. Key Measurable Achievements: Core Banking Migration: Managed the functional requirements for a legacy-to-modern core\nbanking transition for a top-tier institutional bank. Reduced system downtime during main-\ntenance windows by 80 through optimized batch processing logic. AMLKYC Process Re-engineering: Redesigned the Know Your Customer onboarding work-\nflow using BPMN 2.0. Automated 60 of the verification steps, reducing customer onboard-\ning time from 5 days to 4 hours. API Strategy Implementation: Authored the functional specifications for a suite of 200\npublic and private APIs, enabling the banks entry into the Open Banking ecosystem.\nDirectly\nsupported 50M in new partner-driven revenue. UAT Excellence: Directed the User Acceptance Testing (UAT) for a new institutional trading\ndashboard. Managed 150 test users across 5 regions, achieving a Gold\nStatus release with\nzero post-launch critical bugs. Performance Optimization: Collaborated with database architects to optimize\nSQL query\nlogic for real-time risk reports. Reduced report generation time from 5 minutes to 12 seconds", "start_date": null, "end_date": null, "is_current": true}]}
