{"timestamp": "2026-07-08T13:01:05.511230Z", "level": "INFO", "logger": "resume_parser", "message": "\u2705 Experience extraction completed", "request_id": "40da399d-2563-4630-afd7-5f85c2050e97", "experience_count": 1, "experiences": [{"job_title": "Senior Vice President of HR Transformation  Summit Global Logistics", "company_name": "Denver, CO (Leading Global Supply Chain  Logistics Provider  Revenue: 9.4B)", "description": "Strategic Mandate  Executive Oversight: Appointed by the CEO to lead the comprehensive\nmodernization of the global HR function for 18,000 employees across 22 countries.\nResponsible\nfor a 160M HR budget and the supervision of a 120-person HR organization.\nDirect the strategy\nfor talent acquisition, total rewards, labor relations, and HR technology. Key Measurable Achievements: Global HRIS Unification: Orchestrated the 30-month migration from 14 legacy payroll and HR\nsystems to a single global instance of Workday. Achieved a Single Source of\nTruth for people\ndata, reducing manual data entry by 85 and saving 6.5M in annual licensing fees. Strategic Talent Re-Architecture: Redesigned the global talent acquisition strategy, imple-\nmenting an AI-driven sourcing hub and centralized recruitment marketing. Reduced Time-\nto-Hire by 42 and improved quality-of-hire metrics by 28 based on first-year performance\nreviews. Retention  Engagement Transformation: Launched the Summit Peak engagement initia-\ntive, focusing on career pathing and mental health. Improved Year-over-Year (YoY) employee\nengagement scores by 35 and reduced voluntary attrition in high-demand roles by 18. Pay Equity  Transparency: Led a comprehensive global pay equity audit using regression\nanalysis to identify and remediate gender and ethnic pay gaps. Achieved 99.8 pay parity\nacross the organization within 18 months. Executive Succession Planning: Developed a robust succession framework for the top 150\nleadership roles, identifying 2 ready-now internal candidates for 80 of key positions. Re-\nsulted in a 50 increase in internal promotion rates for executive roles.\nESG  DEI Leadership: Integrated DEI metrics into executive compensation triggers. Success-\nfully increased representation of women in Director roles from 22 to 38 in three years. MA Integration Lead: Directed the HR due diligence and cultural integration for the 2.1B\nacquisition of Trans-Euro Freight. Retained 95 of critical talent during the first 12 months\npost-acquisition. Director of Talent  Organizational Development  Meridian Health Systems\nDallas, TX (Integrated Healthcare Network  12,000 Employees)\nOperational Leadership: Served as the strategic head of Talent Management, Learning, and\nOD for a complex healthcare system during a period of rapid expansion and the subsequent\nCOVID-19 crisis. Key Measurable Achievements: Crisis Workforce Strategy: Developed and executed the emergency clinical staffing strategy\nduring the pandemic, including the rapid onboarding of 1,200 travel nurses and the implemen-\ntation of a 247 internal crisis support center. Digital Learning Transformation: Replaced traditional classroom training with a mobile-first\nDigital Learning Ecosystem (LXP). Achieved a 94 adoption rate and reduced training costs per\nemployee by 55 while increasing compliance certifications by 20. Leadership Pipeline Development: Architected the Future-Ready Leader program, a 12-\nmonth intensive development track for high-potential managers. 40 of participants achieved\npromotion within 12 months of graduation. Culture Integration: Led the cultural integration efforts for 4 hospital acquisitions. Stan-\ndardized performance management and values-based behaviors across the network, reducing\npost-merger cultural friction by 60 according to Pulse surveys. Performance Management Redesign: Eliminated annual performance reviews in favor of a\nContinuous Feedback model via a mobile app. Increased manager-employee touchpoints by", "start_date": "2021-07-01", "end_date": null, "is_current": true}]}
